HEADWORD: dolma
<hw>dolma</hw> <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>dolmas</plw>
<it>or</it> <plw>dolmades</plw>.</plu> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>a dish
composed of well-seasoned rice (with nuts or currants of minced lamb)
simmered or braised in stock, stuffed into tomatoes or green peppers, or
wrapped in grape leaves; -- popular in the near east.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> stuffed grape leaves.</syn>⟦br⟧
